pokedexEntries.red: When several of these Pokémon gather, their electricity could build and cause lightning storms.
pokedexEntries.blue: When several of these Pokémon gather, their electricity could build and cause lightning storms.
pokedexEntries.yellow: It keeps its tail raised to monitor its surroundings. If you yank its tail, it will try to bite you.
pokedexEntries.gold: This intelligent Pokémon roasts hard berries with electricity to make them tender enough to eat.
pokedexEntries.silver: It raises its tail to check its surroundings. The tail is sometimes struck by lightning in this pose.
pokedexEntries.crystal: When it is angered, it immediately discharges the energy stored in the pouches in its cheeks.
pokedexEntries.ruby: Whenever Pikachu comes across something new, it blasts it with a jolt of electricity. If you come across a blackened berry, it's evidence that this Pokémon mistook the intensity of its charge.
pokedexEntries.sapphire: This Pokémon has electricity-storing pouches on its cheeks. These appear to become electrically charged during the night while Pikachu sleeps. It occasionally discharges electricity when it is dozy after waking up.
pokedexEntries.emerald: It stores electricity in the electric sacs on its cheeks. When it releases pent-up energy in a burst, the electric power is equal to a lightning bolt.
pokedexEntries.fireRed: It has small electric sacs on both its cheeks. If threatened, it looses electric charges from the sacs.
pokedexEntries.leafGreen: When several of these Pokémon gather, their electricity could build and cause lightning storms.
pokedexEntries.diamond: It lives in forests with others. It stores electricity in the pouches on its cheeks.
pokedexEntries.pearl: If it looses crackling power from the electrical pouches on its cheeks, it is being wary.
pokedexEntries.platinum: It occasionally uses an electric shock to recharge a fellow Pikachu that is in a weakened state.
pokedexEntries.heartGold: This intelligent Pokémon roasts hard berries with electricity to make them tender enough to eat.
pokedexEntries.soulSilver: It raises its tail to check its surroundings. The tail is sometimes struck by lightning in this pose.
pokedexEntries.black: It occasionally uses an electric shock to recharge a fellow Pikachu that is in a weakened state.
pokedexEntries.white: It occasionally uses an electric shock to recharge a fellow Pikachu that is in a weakened state.
pokedexEntries.black2: It occasionally uses an electric shock to recharge a fellow Pikachu that is in a weakened state.
pokedexEntries.white2: It occasionally uses an electric shock to recharge a fellow Pikachu that is in a weakened state.
pokedexEntries.x: It raises its tail to check its surroundings. The tail is sometimes struck by lightning in this pose.
pokedexEntries.y: It has small electric sacs on both its cheeks. If threatened, it looses electric charges from the sacs.
pokedexEntries.omegaRuby: Whenever Pikachu comes across something new, it blasts it with a jolt of electricity. If you come across a blackened berry, it's evidence that this Pokémon mistook the intensity of its charge.
pokedexEntries.alphaSapphire: This Pokémon has electricity-storing pouches on its cheeks. These appear to become electrically charged during the night while Pikachu sleeps. It occasionally discharges electricity when it is dozy after waking up.
pokedexEntries.sun: A plan was recently announced to gather many Pikachu and make an electric power plant.
pokedexEntries.moon: It's in its nature to store electricity. It feels stressed now and then if it's unable to fully discharge the electricity.
pokedexEntries.ultraSun: Its nature is to store up electricity. Forests where nests of Pikachu live are dangerous, since the trees are so often struck by lightning.
pokedexEntries.ultraMoon: While sleeping, it generates electricity in the sacs in its cheeks. If it’s not getting enough sleep, it will be able to use only weak electricity.
